      "title": "Desert Locust Swarm — Active Outbreak in Rajasthan & Gujarat Border",
      "description": "A large swarm of Desert Locusts estimated at 150–200 sq km has crossed from Pakistan into Barmer, Jaisalmer, and Kutch districts. The swarm is moving in a south-easterly direction at approximately 90–150 km/day, driven by south-westerly winds. Flash gregarization of juveniles (hoppers) has been observed near Bikaner. IMD wind trajectory models suggest the swarm may reach northern Maharashtra within 5–7 days if not controlled.",
      "detected_at": "2024-07-12T08:30:00+05:30",
      "last_updated": "2024-07-14T07:00:00+05:30",
      "origin": "Pakistan (Sindh Province)",
